---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceExplore from '../../components/ServiceExplore.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Pediatric Dentistry — Oasis Dental Care, Huntington Beach"
  description="Gentle, friendly pediatric dental care in Huntington Beach for infants, children, and teens. Dr. Jason Fu at Oasis Dental Care. Call (714) 893-2106."
  page="services"
>

<section class="phero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumbs"><a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/services">Services</a><span class="sep">/</span><span style="color:#cfe6e2">Pediatric Dentistry</span></div>
    <span class="tag">Pediatric dentistry</span>
    <h1>Pediatric Dentistry</h1>
    <p>Building healthy smiles and positive dental habits from day one.</p>
    <div class="acts">
      <a class="btn" href="/contact">Book your child's first visit <svg class="ico" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg></a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="tel:7148932106">Call (714) 893-2106</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="pad">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="split">
      <div>

        <div class="img-ph reveal">
          <div class="img-ph-ic"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="3"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="9" r="1.5"/><path d="m21 15-5-5L5 21"/></svg></div>
          <span class="img-ph-lbl">Photo placeholder</span>
          <span class="img-ph-desc">Child smiling in dental chair with parent nearby — warm, bright setting</span>
        </div>

        <div class="prose reveal">
          <span class="tag">Overview</span>
          <h2>Gentle, specialized care for your child's smile.</h2>
          <p>Pediatric dentistry covers specialized dental care for infants, children, and teens in a way that's positive, supportive, and tailored to their unique needs—from baby teeth checkups to early orthodontic guidance.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="prose reveal" style="margin-top:48px">
          <h3>What We Cover</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>First dental visit for infants and toddlers</li>
            <li>Cleanings, exams, and X-rays for children</li>
            <li>Fluoride treatments and sealants</li>
            <li>Cavity prevention and education</li>
            <li>Early orthodontic evaluation (ages 7+)</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="img-ph reveal">
            <div class="img-ph-ic"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="3"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="9" r="1.5"/><path d="m21 15-5-5L5 21"/></svg></div>
            <span class="img-ph-lbl">Photo placeholder</span>
            <span class="img-ph-desc">Child in dental chair, smiling — friendly team member nearby</span>
          </div>

          <h3>When Should My Child First Visit?</h3>
          <p>The American Academy of Pediatric Dentistry recommends a first visit by the child's first birthday, or within 6 months of the first tooth appearing. Starting early builds positive associations and lets us catch any early concerns.</p>

          <h3>Our Approach with Kids</h3>
          <p>We take time to introduce equipment, explain steps in kid-friendly language, and create a visit that feels fun rather than scary. Parents are welcome in the room. We believe a child's first dental experiences shape how they feel about oral health for life.</p>

          <div class="img-ph reveal">
            <div class="img-ph-ic"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="3"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="9" r="1.5"/><path d="m21 15-5-5L5 21"/></svg></div>
            <span class="img-ph-lbl">Photo placeholder</span>
            <span class="img-ph-desc">Team member showing a child a dental tool in a playful, reassuring way</span>
          </div>

          <h3>Sealants &amp; Fluoride</h3>
          <p>Sealants protect the grooves of back teeth where cavities most often form. Fluoride treatments strengthen enamel. Both are quick, painless, and highly effective for cavity prevention.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal" style="margin-top:48px">
          <span class="tag">Common questions</span>
          <h2 class="prose" style="margin-top:8px">Good to know.</h2>
          <div class="faq">
            <details open><summary>When should my child first see a dentist?</summary><p>By their first birthday or within six months of their first tooth appearing. Early visits help establish healthy habits and catch any concerns early.</p></details>
            <details><summary>What if my child is scared of the dentist?</summary><p>We're experienced with anxious kids. We go slowly, explain everything in simple terms, and make the visit feel as normal and fun as possible.</p></details>
            <details><summary>Are dental X-rays safe for children?</summary><p>Yes. We use digital X-rays, which emit minimal radiation. We only take them when clinically necessary and appropriate for the child's age.</p></details>
            <details><summary>When should we start an orthodontic evaluation?</summary><p>The American Association of Orthodontists recommends a first orthodontic evaluation around age 7, when we can identify early alignment issues before they become harder to treat.</p></details>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <aside>
        <div class="scard reveal">
          <div class="hd"><div class="grid-ov"></div><h3>Book your child's first visit</h3><p>We love welcoming young patients</p></div>
          <div class="bd">
            <div class="row"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M12 7v5l3 2"/></svg><span>First visits typically 30–45 min</span></div>
            <div class="row"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 6 9 17l-5-5"/></svg><span>Most insurance accepted &amp; verified</span></div>
            <div class="row"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 2 4 5v6c0 5 3.5 9 8 11 4.5-2 8-6 8-11V5l-8-3z"/></svg><span>Gentle, kid-friendly techniques</span></div>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <a class="btn" href="/contact">Book Your Child's First Visit</a>
            <a class="btn btn-out" href="tel:7148932106" style="justify-content:center">Call (714) 893-2106</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<ServiceExplore />

</Layout>
